<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Head, pronotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[577,699,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 20" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,326,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1424,323,1942]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 20. Dosal and lateral habitus and face. 1, 6, 11, 16: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 2, 7, 12, 17: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 3, 8, 13, 18: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 4, 9, 14, 19: T. quadragulatus sp. n.; 5, 10, 15, 20: T. luchunensis sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199897/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Figs 4, 19</figureCitation>
) light brown, with obvious oyster white longitudinal streak on vertex medially; forewing (
<figureCitation box="[457,538,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 54" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[152,1431,181,1364]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,175,1367]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 54. Ovipositor and forewing. 46 – 47: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang, second valvulae and apex of second valvulae respectively, lateral view; 48 – 49: first valvulae and apex of first valvulae respectively, laterior view; 50: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 51: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 52: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 53: T. quadragulatus sp. n.; 54: T. luchunensis sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199899/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[509,538,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
) with pale yellow plaque only in the costal area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[370,452,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[423,452,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
) nearly quadrangular in lateral view, densely with row of microsetae on apex. Apex of footlike apical process of style short and robust, about one sixth length of style (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1164,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[1132,1164,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft 
<emphasis box="[1364,1436,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">in situ</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,287,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Figs 
<number box="[215,287,295,319]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="37.5" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="37.0">37–38</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin not concave in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[201,1064,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,574]" box="[201,1064,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
